                <p>Digital images are stored as matrices! Each pixel is a number representing color. Matrix operations help blur, sharpen, or transform images!</p>
                
                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Example 2: Recommendation Systems</strong></p>
                <p>Netflix uses matrices where rows = users, columns = movies, values = ratings. Matrix operations help find similar users and recommend movies!</p>
                
                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Example 3: Google Search</strong></p>
                <p>Google uses massive matrices to rank web pages. Each web page connection is stored in a matrix, and operations help determine which pages are most important!</p>
